The paper discusses the Archives Unleashed project, which focuses on improving scholarly access to web archives through tool creation, process modeling, and community building. The main contribution of the paper is a process model that decomposes scholarly inquiries into four main activities: filter, extract, aggregate, and visualize. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
